{% comment %}
  sections/banner.liquid
  ------------------------------------------------------------------
  Global header strip + hero banner + bottom strip for "The Gift
  Guide" page. Built from scratch (no Dawn section reuse), per hard
  constraint in the build-context doc §2. All copy is customizer-
  editable via schema settings — nothing hardcoded in the markup.

  Depends on:
    - assets/custom-sections.js → initMobileHeaderToggle() wires the
      hamburger/X toggle for the mobile two-state header.
    - assets/custom-sections.css → shared reset rules only; all
      section-specific styling lives in the {% style %} block below.

  Scaling note (see build-context doc §4a/§8 "scaling caveat"):
  the Figma type values (164.78px heading / 47.08px description) were
  read off a 3,840px artboard that's very likely a 2x+ export canvas,
  not the literal browser width. Rather than hardcode a single px
  value that could be wildly wrong depending on the real render width,
  headline/description sizing below uses `clamp()` scaled toward the
  ~1920px-reference numbers the build-context doc itself suggests
  (~82px / ~24px). Confirm against the live page once it's up and
  adjust the clamp() bounds if needed — this is a deliberate stand-in,
  not a literal Figma pixel value. Button sizes (244x44, 24x24 header
  height fractions) are used at face value since the doc only flagged
  *type* values as needing rescaling, not UI chrome.

  Illustration background — desktop vs. mobile SVGs:
  Figma provides two separate line-art illustration exports, not one
  asset reused at different sizes — a wide/landscape composition for
  desktop (icons scattered across the full hero width, positioned top
  right per the layout below) and a narrower/taller composition for
  the stacked mobile hero (see build-context doc §4a mobile section:
  illustration sits as its own strip below the heading/description,
  with "SHOP NOW" floating on it). These are fixed design assets, not
  merchant content, so they ship as permanent theme files —
  `assets/banner-illustration-desktop.svg` and
  `assets/banner-illustration-mobile.svg` — referenced directly via
  `asset_url` rather than through the Theme Editor. Desktop renders
  its SVG as a CSS background-image on `.banner__hero` (unchanged
  below). Mobile renders its SVG as a real `<img>` inside
  `.banner__hero-illustration` instead — see that section's
  markup/CSS for why a background-image doesn't work for mobile's
  real-layout-element requirement. Both assets always exist as part
  of the theme, so no blank/fallback state is needed for either.
{% endcomment %}

<section class="banner__section section-{{ section.id }}" data-section-id="{{ section.id }}" data-section-type="banner">

  {%- comment %} ── Global header bar (wordmark / tagline / CHOOSE GIFT) ── {% endcomment -%}
  <div class="banner__header">
    <div class="banner__content">
        <span class="banner__wordmark">{{ section.settings.wordmark }}</span>

        {%- comment %} Mobile-only hamburger/X toggle. Hidden on desktop via CSS. {% endcomment -%}
        <button
        type="button"
        class="banner__nav-toggle"
        data-nav-toggle
        aria-expanded="false"
        aria-controls="BannerHeaderExpand-{{ section.id }}"
        aria-label="Toggle menu"
      >
        <span class="banner__nav-icon-open">{% render 'icon-hamburger' %}</span>
        <span class="banner__nav-icon-close">{% render 'icon-close' %}</span>
      </button>

      {%- comment %}
        Desktop: display:contents dissolves this wrapper so tagline and
        header-expand become direct children of the 3-column header-row
        grid (auto 1fr auto) — that's what makes the tagline sit truly
        centered, independent of the button group's width. Mobile: the
        wrapper becomes a real flex column, hidden by default and toggled
        via data-expanded by initMobileHeaderToggle() in gift-guide.js
        (aria-controls above points at this element's id).
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="banner__header-expand" id="BannerHeaderExpand-{{ section.id }}" data-nav-expand>
        <p class="banner__tagline">{{ section.settings.tagline }}</p>
        <div class="banner__cta-group">
          <a href="{{ section.settings.header_button_link | default: '#' }}" class="banner__button banner__button--yellow">
            {{ section.settings.header_button_label }} {% render 'icon-arrow' %}
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {%- comment %}
    ── Hero banner content ──
    Structure: Hero > Text (heading/description) + Illustration (image/SHOP NOW).
    Desktop keeps its illustration as a `.banner__hero` CSS background
    (unchanged, see the {% style %} block below) and visually ignores
    `.banner__hero-illustration`'s <img> (hidden at the desktop
    breakpoint) — the wrapper exists in markup for both so the DOM
    only renders once, but each breakpoint uses a different mechanism
    for the same asset: desktop = background-image, mobile = a real
    <img> with natural height (see mobile media query for why).
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="banner__hero">
    <div class="banner__content">
      <div class="banner__hero-text">
        <h1 class="banner__heading">{{ section.settings.heading }}</h1>
        {%- comment %} Desktop shows the full paragraph; mobile shows a shorter, single-sentence version per the Figma mobile frame — same desktop/mobile toggle pattern as the bottom strip below. {% endcomment -%}
        <div class="banner__description banner__description--desktop">{{ section.settings.description }}</div>
        <div class="banner__description banner__description--mobile">{{ section.settings.description_mobile }}</div>
      </div>

      <div class="banner__hero-illustration">
        {%- comment %}
          Mobile-only real <img> (desktop hides this and keeps using
          its existing background-image approach instead — see
          {% style %}). Static theme asset, guaranteed to exist — no
          conditional or fallback needed. width/height below are the
          SVG's intrinsic dimensions (required by theme-check's
          ImgWidthAndHeight rule) — CSS still forces width:100%;
          height:auto at render time, so these only set the aspect
          ratio for layout/CLS purposes. Update if the source SVG's
          own viewBox dimensions differ.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <img
          src="{{ 'banner-illustration-mobile.svg' | asset_url }}"
          alt=""
          role="presentation"
          loading="lazy"
          width="800"
          height="600"
          class="banner__hero-illustration-image"
        >

        <a href="{{ section.settings.banner_button_link | default: '#' }}" class="banner__button banner__button--black">
          {{ section.settings.banner_button_label }} {% render 'icon-arrow' %}
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {%- comment %}
    ── Bottom strip ──
    Confirmed via Figma that mobile and desktop bottom-strip copy is
    NOT the same string (desktop: "...CLOTHES IN SIZES XXS TO 6XL",
    mobile: "...ACTIVEWEAR") — so this needs two independent settings,
    toggled by CSS display at the same 480px breakpoint used
    elsewhere, rather than one shared string.
  {% endcomment -%}
  <div class="banner__bottom-strip">
    <p class="banner__bottom-strip-text banner__bottom-strip-text--desktop">{{ section.settings.bottom_strip_text }}</p>
    <p class="banner__bottom-strip-text banner__bottom-strip-text--mobile">{{ section.settings.bottom_strip_text_mobile }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{%- comment %}
  Loaded once here since Banner is always the first section on the
  Gift Guide page (see templates/page.gift-guide.json) — avoids
  loading gift-guide.js/css a second time from product-grid.liquid or
  snippets/product-popup.liquid.
{% endcomment -%}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'gift-guide.css' | asset_url }}">
<script src="{{ 'gift-guide.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>

{% style %}
  .section-{{ section.id }} {
    background: #ffffff;
  }

  /* Header bar */
  .banner__header {
    background: #f5f5f5;
    padding: 1.75rem 2.5rem; /* taller bar than before — matches the reference's breathing room */
  }
  /* This is the actual fix for the header layout — .banner__content is
    reused for both the header AND the hero, and only ever had
    max-width/position set on it (no display:grid), so the
    justify-self rules on wordmark/tagline/cta-group below were doing
    nothing and everything was just stacking as normal block content.
    Scoped to .banner__header so it doesn't affect the hero's use of
     the same class. */
  @media (min-width: 481px) {
    .banner__header .banner__content {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
      align-items: center;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: none; /* overrides the 560px hero constraint in this context */
      column-gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
  .banner__wordmark {
    font-family: 'Jost', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em; /* the gap between "TISSO" and "VISON" in the reference */
    text-transform: uppercase;
    justify-self: start;
  }
  .banner__tagline {
    font-family: 'Jost', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #000000;
    justify-self: center;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .banner__content {
    max-width: 560px;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .banner__header-expand {
    /* Desktop: dissolve the wrapper so .banner__tagline and .banner__cta-group
      become direct grid items of header-row's auto/1fr/auto tracks — this is
       what makes the tagline center independently of the button group. */
    display: contents;
  }
  .banner__header-inner {
    width: 100%;
  }
  .banner__tagline {
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .banner__cta-group {
    justify-self: end;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .banner__nav-toggle {
    display: none; /* shown only in the mobile breakpoint below */
    background: none;
    border: none;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .banner__nav-icon-close { display: none; }
  .banner__nav-toggle[aria-expanded="true"] .banner__nav-icon-open { display: none; }
  .banner__nav-toggle[aria-expanded="true"] .banner__nav-icon-close { display: inline; }

  .banner__cta-group .banner__button--yellow {
    width: 180px; /* adjust to match your real render — reference shows it wider than a tight text-fit button */
    height: 48px;
  }

  /* Buttons — used at face value (see scaling note above) */
  .icon-arrow {
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin-left: 0.5em;
    transition: color 300ms ease-out;
  }

  .banner__button {
    position: relative;
    isolation: isolate;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 244px;
    height: 44px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: 'Jost', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color 300ms ease-out;
  }
  .banner__button::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: -1;
    transform: scaleX(0);
    transform-origin: right center;
    transition: transform 300ms ease-out;
  }
  .banner__button:hover::before,
  .banner__button:focus-visible::before {
    transform: scaleX(1);
    transform-origin: left center;
  }
  .banner__button--yellow { background: #fff544; color: #000000; }
  .banner__button--yellow::before { background: #000000; }
  .banner__button--yellow:hover,
  .banner__button--yellow:focus-visible { color: #fff544; }

  .banner__button--black { background: #000000; color: #ffffff; }
  .banner__button--black::before { background: #fff544; }
  .banner__button--black:hover,
  .banner__button--black:focus-visible { color: #000000; }

  /* Hero */
  .banner__hero {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 34rem; /* tune against your live page — this is what gives the illustration room to show above the text */
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;   /* text sits at the BOTTOM of the hero, not centered */
    justify-content: flex-start;
    padding: 3rem 4rem;
    background-image: url('{{ "banner-illustration-desktop.svg" | asset_url }}');
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: top right; /* keeps the icon cluster up/right, clear space stays bottom-left */
    background-size: contain;
  }
  .banner__content {
    max-width: 560px;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .banner__heading {
    font-family: 'Jost', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 4vw, 4.25rem); /* ~64-68px at typical desktop widths */
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .banner__description {
    font-family: 'Jost', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1rem; /* ~16px, not fluid — stays small and steady per the reference */
    line-height: 1.4;
    max-width: 20rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .banner__description--mobile {
    display: none; /* desktop shows the full paragraph by default */
  }

  .banner__illustration {
    min-width: 0; /* lets the grid track actually shrink the image instead of overflowing */
  }
  .banner__illustration img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Desktop: .banner__hero-text and .banner__hero-illustration are new
    wrapper divs (added so mobile can treat the illustration as a real
    layout element — see mobile media query below) but desktop's visual
    output must stay byte-for-byte identical to before this refactor.
    display: contents dissolves both wrappers so heading/description/
    button fall back to being direct children of .banner__content,
    exactly as they were pre-refactor, and the illustration <img>
    (mobile-only content) is hidden outright since desktop keeps using
    its existing .banner__hero background-image instead. */
  .banner__hero-text,
  .banner__hero-illustration {
    display: contents;
  }
  .banner__hero-illustration-image {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Bottom strip */
  .banner__bottom-strip {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-family: 'Jost', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #eeeeee;
  }
  .banner__bottom-strip-text {
    margin: 0;
  }
  .banner__bottom-strip-text--mobile {
    display: none; /* desktop copy shown by default */
  }

  /* Mobile — Frame 1, 402px fixed width per §4a Dev Mode inspect.
    Stacked order confirmed: header → heading → description →
    illustration (w/ SHOP NOW overlaid) → bottom strip. */
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .banner__heading {
      font-size: 1.875rem; /* 30px */
      line-height: 1; /* 100% */
      margin: 0 0 1.5rem; /* 24px gap to description (103px - (49px + 30px)) */
    }
    .banner__description {
      font-size: 1rem; /* 16px */
      line-height: 1.3; /* 130% */
      max-width: 21.25rem; /* 340px */
      margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    }
    .banner__description--desktop {
      display: none;
    }
    .banner__description--mobile {
      display: block;
    }

    .banner__header .banner__content {
      position: relative;
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .banner__nav-toggle {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 0;
      height: 2rem;
    }

    .banner__nav-icon-open svg {
      display: block;
      width: 18px;
      height: 11px;
    }
    .banner__nav-icon-close svg {
      display: block;
      width: 14px;
      height: 14px;
    }

    .banner__header-expand {
      display: none;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      flex-basis: 100%;
      width: 100%;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .banner__header-expand[data-expanded="true"] {
      display: flex;
    }

    .banner__tagline {
      justify-self: auto;
      margin: 0;
      white-space: normal;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .banner__cta-group {
      justify-self: auto;
      width: 100%;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .banner__header-expand .banner__button {
      width: 244px;
      max-width: 85%;
      margin: 0 auto 0.75rem;
    }

    /* ── Hero, mobile ──────────────────────────────────────────────
      Illustration is now a real layout element (a genuine <img>, see
      markup above) instead of a CSS background — a background-image
      on a fixed-height box has no intrinsic size for the browser to
      lay out against, which is what previously produced a large gap
      above the image and pushed the expandable header out of view.
      An <img> in normal flow sizes itself from its own aspect ratio,
      so no min-height guess is needed here at all.

      .banner__content becomes the vertical stack: text block, then
      illustration block, in source order — no absolute positioning
      needed at this level anymore. */
    .banner__hero {
      min-height: 0;
      align-items: flex-start;
      background-image: none;
      padding: 3.0625rem 1.25rem 0; /* 49px, per Dev Mode Top on the heading */
    }
    .banner__hero .banner__content {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
      max-width: none;
    }

    /* Text block: plain white zone, heading + description only. */
    .banner__hero-text {
      display: block; /* overrides the desktop-only `display: contents` above */
      width: 100%;
    }

    /* Illustration block: image + SHOP NOW, positioned relative to
      *this* container rather than the whole hero — so the button
      always sits on the image regardless of the image's own height. */
    .banner__hero-illustration {
      display: block; /* overrides the desktop-only `display: contents` above */
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }
    .banner__hero-illustration-image {
      display: block; /* overrides the desktop-only `display: none` above */
      width: 100%;
      height: auto; /* natural aspect ratio — no fixed/guessed height */
    }
    .banner__hero-illustration .banner__button {
      position: absolute;
      left: 50%;
      bottom: 2rem;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      width: auto;
      min-width: 155px;
    }

    .banner__bottom-strip {
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }
    .banner__bottom-strip-text--desktop { display: none; }
    .banner__bottom-strip-text--mobile { display: block; }

    .banner__button { transition: none; }
    .banner__button::before { display: none; }
    .banner__button--yellow:hover,
    .banner__button--yellow:focus-visible { color: #000000; }
    .banner__button--black:hover,
    .banner__button--black:focus-visible { color: #ffffff; }
  }
{% endstyle %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Banner",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "wordmark",
      "label": "Wordmark / logo text",
      "default": "TISSO VISON"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "tagline",
      "label": "Header tagline",
      "default": "Find the ideal gift for your loved ones."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "header_button_label",
      "label": "Header button label",
      "default": "CHOOSE GIFT"
    },
    {
      "type": "url",
      "id": "header_button_link",
      "label": "Header button link"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "default": "The Gift Guide"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "description",
      "label": "Description",
      "default": "<p>Discover Joy: Your Ultimate Holiday Gift Destination. Explore our curated selection and find the perfect gifts to delight your loved ones this holiday season.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "description_mobile",
      "label": "Description (mobile)",
      "info": "Shown only on mobile in place of the full description — Figma's mobile frame uses a shorter, single-sentence version rather than the full desktop paragraph.",
      "default": "<p>Discover Joy: Your Ultimate Holiday Gift Destination.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "banner_button_label",
      "label": "Banner button label",
      "default": "SHOP NOW"
    },
    {
      "type": "url",
      "id": "banner_button_link",
      "label": "Banner button link"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "bottom_strip_text",
      "label": "Bottom strip text (desktop)",
      "default": "SUSTAINABLE, ETHICALLY MADE CLOTHES IN SIZES XXS TO 6XL"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "bottom_strip_text_mobile",
      "label": "Bottom strip text (mobile)",
      "info": "Confirmed different from the desktop copy in the Figma mobile frame — not a truncated version, a distinct string.",
      "default": "SUSTAINABLE, ETHICALLY MADE ACTIVEWEAR"
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Banner"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
